description:
Michael Czechowski is a man who divides opinion. He was the first Adventist to go to Europe as a missionary, and accomplished a lot in his relatively short life. However, he did not go with the blessing of the Seventh Day Adventist Church. Whilst he had many good traits of character, there are also some lessons that can be gleaned from his life.

To find out more information about Michael Czechowski, please read our extended article on our website.
